<section class="home-panel">
    <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
    <p>Over 100,000 Byzantine seals are housed in a wide array of collections, many of which are only partially published or presented across scattered books, articles or platforms. For the first time, this Portal offers a unified entry point, allowing these dispersed holdings to be comprehensively searched—and unlocking new avenues for research.</p>
    <p>The lack of publicly accessible information on seals has long been a major gap in Byzantine sigillography. This initiative responds to that need by offering a user-friendly and pragmatic platform for sharing data, with minimal requirements for participation.</p>
    <p>Every seal description remains clearly credited to its respective contributor, who retains full responsibility for the content.</p>
    <p>With CSÆB, you can search a metacorpus comprising potentially tens of thousands of seals from various collections—all in a single click.</p>
</section>

<section class="home-panel">
    <h2>Getting started</h2>
    <p>Get in touch with the DigiByzSeal project team.</p>
    <p>We will support you in exploring the most suitable option and guide you in preparing your data to meet the minimal participation standards.</p>
    <p>Our goal is to make contributing as easy and accessible as possible.</p>
</section>

